# mquantum environment variables.
#
# All variables are optional. The build runs without any of them; values
# below are starting points for local experiments.
#
# Vite-exposed variables MUST be prefixed `VITE_` to be readable from
# the browser bundle (anything else is server-only, but this project is
# pure-client and has no server).

# Build provenance — short git SHA injected by `vite.config.ts` via
# `import.meta.env.VITE_GIT_SHA`. Hermetic / CI environments without a
# `git` binary on PATH should set this explicitly so the SRMT sweep
# reproducibility manifest carries a non-`unknown` revision.
# VITE_GIT_SHA=

# Reserved for future use — not currently consumed by any module.
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
